Key Match Events: The match between South Africa and Zimbabwe ended with no result due to rain.
South Africa scored 51/0 in 3 overs chasing a target of 64.
Pre-Game Insights: Rain was anticipated to affect the match between South Africa and Zimbabwe.
South Africa were the favorites, having never lost a T20I to Zimbabwe.
This was Zimbabwe's first major tournament under coach Dave Houghton.
South Africa's coach Mark Boucher was set to leave after this tournament to join Mumbai Indians.
Temba Bavuma, South Africa's captain, was under scrutiny due to his recent poor form.
Sikandar Raza was highlighted as a key player for Zimbabwe, having performed exceptionally well in recent months.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The pitch at Bellerive Oval was noted to be difficult for scoring off the new ball.
Weather conditions were cold and rainy in Hobart, affecting the match.
Zimbabwe have never beaten South Africa in a T20I.
Luke Jongwe was two wickets away from fifty T20I wickets.
